The course provides an advanced-level overview to the current research themes in the fields of pharmaceutical and related sciences. The course will also train the student to follow oral scientific presentations in the scientific podium. During the course, the student participates at least in seven (7) seminars, acts as a discussion moderator in one seminar, and participate in one excursion to pharmaceutical industry, companies or institutions (+ written report).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to introduce and provide overview to the current research trends in pharmaceutical sciences by presenting a wide range of research themes in the different fields of pharmaceutical and related sciences.  The student will also learn to get to know oral presentations and discussion in the scientific podium as well as to write an excursion report.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The MSc/PhD student who has passed the 	course: -	have an overview on the up-to-date research topics and areas in pharmaceutical sciences carried out in Estonia  -	knows the general practices and methods to prepare an oral scientific presentation -	understands the added value of scientific discussion and participating in scientific meetings
